values.value: Webcam Arm Motion Detection (addon for Hebi's ArmSway) by Lunazera v1.1 - Nov 9 2023 ▼——————————————— ▼ Arm Motion tracking for ArmSway. Works with webcam arm tracking and external tracking systems. Should also generally work when animations are played or poses are applied using the Set Pose node. Load Order: Place directly after ArmSway Features: • Works alongside ArmSway • Sends out MotionTriggered and MotionLost triggers that can be used in other graphs • Has buffer when tracking is lost (settings below) (if you want to run this standalone, wire the cyan Application Start node into the Start Timer node)

Arm Motion Tracking Logic: 1. Get the rotation values 2. Subtract pose rotation from tracked rotation values. • If the arms rotation = default OR pose, then both these values should be 0. This will indicate that arms are not being tracked. 3. Calculate Sin of values, switching from degrees to radians, and deviation in either direction goes +/-1 4. Check two filters to see if the value is past the sensitivity amount (in either + or - directions). • First, check if arm is in the default down pose, which model always returns to when tracking is lost. • If motion away from this default, then next checks to see if the motion is moved away from the pose. 5. If shoulder or lower arm motion is detected, or leap motion is detected, then a single Motion Triggered trigger is called for either the right or left arm separately. 6. Once motion is lost after being detected, a single Motion Lost trigger is called for either the right or left arm separately. Changelog: • Added experimental motion-based tracking detection, mainly for webcam tracking. Works with leapmotion tracking as well (external tracking might also work I think). Also by how it works will likely turn off armsway when animations are played that move the arms. • Further cleaned this to have smoother on/off detection. • Changed upperarm to shoulder, as upperarm rotation values were kinda weird. • Added short buffer time when tracking is lost for when it starts looking again. • Added check for pose as well as default down position v1.1 • Removed Leap Motion related nodes (this is just built into ArmSway now)

↑↑ ↑↑ These parameters set how sensitive the motion tracking is (how much you need to move your models arms away from the pose until it activates) • lower value = more sensitive, movement detected sooner Tracking Triggers: There are triggers you can use if you want to use the arm tracking detection in other graphs. These triggers will activate only once when activated, and once when lost. • LeftMotionTriggered • RightMotionTriggered • LeftMotionLost • RightMotionLost Also, there are buffer triggers if you need a longer time window before the arm tracking starts working again. • RightMotionBuffer • LeftMotionBuffer
